text: Six World Trade Center, building 6 of the World Trade Center in New York City was a U.S. Customhouse. It was completed in 1972 at a height of 105 ft (32 m). It was heavily damaged during the September 11, 2001 attacks by the collapse of the North Tower at 10:28 a.m. EDT and later demolished in December 2001.
